This course provides an advanced-level approach to Industrial pharmacy and pharmaceutical industry as a business branch. The course will provide an insight into  the basic operations of the pharmaceutical industry including (but not limited to) pharmaceutical product development, formulation development, manufacturing (production) and process engineering, quality management and quality standards, packaging technology, regulatory issues, industrial plant design, distribution (wholesale) operations, clinical studies, and marketing strategies of pharmaceuticals.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to provide an advanced-level knowledge on Industrial pharmacy and pharmaceutical industry as a business branch. The course presents a wide range of fundamental operations of the pharmaceutical industry, such as pharmaceutical product development, formulation development, industrial-scale manufacturing and process development, quality management, quality control and assurance, packaging operations, legislation background and regulatory issues, industrial plant design, distribution (wholesale) operations, clinical studies, and marketing strategies of pharmaceuticals.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The MSc/PhD student who has passed the course: -	knows the key functions and operations of the pharmaceutical industry  -	has an overview on  pharmaceutical product development, formulation development, and industrial-scale  manufacturing and packaging of pharmaceuticals   -	knows the principles of quality management and quality standards (incl. Good Manufacturing Practices, GMP and Good Laboratory Practices, GLP) -	has an overview on the key EU and national legislation and regulatory settings related to industrial-scale manufacturing of pharmaceuticals  -	knows the wholesale operations related to pharmaceuticals -	knows the marketing strategies and practices of pharmaceuticals .
